# Web Accessibility And SEO

- Use semantic HTML for interactive and landmark elements (`button`, `main`, `nav`, `form`, `label`).
- Add ARIA only when semantic HTML is not enough.
- Preserve keyboard access, focus order, and visible focus states.
- Maintain WCAG AA contrast for text and important UI controls.
- For routed web pages, keep page titles, descriptions, canonical links, and OpenGraph metadata current when the framework supports them.
- Test accessibility-critical changes with the project’s available tooling or browser inspection workflow.
